               <p>I am the wife of 
               <persName id="t17760522-38-person492">
                  Jacob
                   Otto
               <interp inst="t17760522-38-person492" type="surname" value="Otto"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-38-person492" type="given" value="Jacob"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-38-person492" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ; I let a ready furnished room, up three pair of stairs, to the prisoner, at half a crown a week; the things mentioned in the indictment were in the lodging; I went into the room and missed the things; I asked her what she had done with them; she said she had pawned them; I have recovered several of them.</p>
               <p>[
               <persName id="t17760522-38-person493">
                  Robert
                   Arlz
               <interp inst="t17760522-38-person493" type="surname" value="Arlz"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-38-person493" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-38-person493" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , a pawnbroker, produced the curtains and sheet, which had been pawned with him by the prisoner, and they were deposed to by the prosecutor.]</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I pawned them with an intent to fetch them out again, but my landlady took me to the watch-house and would not let me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17760522-38-verdict171" type="verdictDescription">
